  "explanation": "The defendant committed a serious breach of trust by embezzling $25,000 from their employer. While white-collar crimes require an element of deterrence, the court must weigh the significant mitigating factors present in this case. The defendant has no prior criminal record and has already made efforts to partially repay the stolen funds, demonstrating remorse and a willingness to make the victim whole. Balancing the need for punishment and general deterrence with the defendant's rehabilitation potential and ongoing restitution efforts, a short period of incarceration is appropriate.",
